                                   Fishing
    Fishing is an art form. Not everyone can just grab a stick, some twine,
and stick some glob of something on the end of a hook... NO!

    You must buy a real fishing pole, and some real bait. Once you've found
the proper place to fish, bait your hook and cast your line. When something
bites, fight it to the shore.

    Commands:
      bait hook   - put a glob of bait on your hook
      fish        - cast your line (opens the Fishing panel on the web
                    client)
      fish stop   - give up on the current session

    Fishing works in beach, swamp, lake, sea, river, and underwater terrain.

Playing on the web client (play.darkwind.ai):
    Typing 'fish' opens the Fishing panel. Hold to charge your cast - more
power reaches rarer fish, but they fight harder. When the bobber plunges,
hook the fish fast, then hold and release to keep your line on the fish as
it runs. Watch the tension meter: too tight and the line snaps, too slack
and the fish wriggles free. Fill the catch bar to land it.

Playing from other clients:
    The same 'bait hook' and 'fish' commands work anywhere; your cast
resolves on its own after a few moments.

What you can catch:
    Sixteen species swim Darkwind's waters, from the humble mud toad fish
to legends like the Leviathan Fry - each with its own waters, moods, and
fight. Rarer fish demand higher Fishing skill to even take your hook. Every
fish can be eaten (better catches nourish more) or sold, and a clean fight
lands a higher-quality catch.

Getting started:
  1. Buy a fishing pole and bait in the profession building, 4e, n from
     Center of Town.
  2. Travel to beach, swamp, lake, sea, river, or underwater terrain.
  3. Use 'bait hook', then 'fish'.
  4. Land the fish!

    Your Fishing skill improves with successful catches. Higher skill
attracts rarer fish, quickens their bite, steadies your line, and raises
the quality of what you land.

    Successful catches can also recover profession reagents from the fish:
fish bones, fish gills, bloody fins, and fish tails.

    Fishing materials can be used by recipe cards, guildcraft, and
profession work orders. Fishing workers can also gather fish-part reagents
for you over time.

    Enjoy! And, be careful about those fish lies. We all know the truth.
